  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n      \t\t\t\t\t\u003cul\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cli id=\"Entry1\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ca name=\"entry\" id=\"EntryAnchor\"\u003eanchor\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/6c/6cb74dfc4e6fdb336f556d7fa0136e9f.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\" title=\"Photo by Rafael Soldi Photography\" data-size=\"1069x1620\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cimg srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/6c/6cb74dfc4e6fdb336f556d7fa0136e9f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/6c/6cb74dfc4e6fdb336f556d7fa0136e9f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/6c/6cb74dfc4e6fdb336f556d7fa0136e9f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\" src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/6c/6cb74dfc4e6fdb336f556d7fa0136e9f.jpg?fit=crop\u0026amp;auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" title=\"Photo by Rafael Soldi Photography\" alt=\"Photo by Rafael Soldi Photography\" width=\"514\" height=\"\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003ePhoto by Rafael Soldi Photography\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eA new home in \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/news/tag/7932/seattle\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eSeattle\u003c/a\u003e’s Mt. Baker neighborhood from \u003ca href=\"https://archinect.com/firms/cover/15643963/best-practice-architecture\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eBest Practice Architecture\u003c/a\u003e dubbed \u0026#39;Lil Shingle\u0026#39; was completed earlier this year at 2,617 square feet. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe home, an early-1950s vestige that was salvaged after falling into a state of considerable disrepair, derives its name from the custom-made scalloped cedar facade shingles featured in the new design. Its past degradation had earned it the dubious moniker \u0026#34;Slanty Shanty.\u0026#34;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/0d/0dbfa4c734a54c5df0991c604c465f2d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x600\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/0d/0dbfa4c734a54c5df0991c604c465f2d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/0d/0dbfa4c734a54c5df0991c604c465f2d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/0d/0dbfa4c734a54c5df0991c604c465f2d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/0d/0dbfa4c734a54c5df0991c604c465f2d.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto by Rafael Soldi Photography\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/85/85c3267c6e2b9b05d76e72634348e5a6.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x1466\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/85/85c3267c6e2b9b05d76e72634348e5a6.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/85/85c3267c6e2b9b05d76e72634348e5a6.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/85/85c3267c6e2b9b05d76e72634348e5a6.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/85/85c3267c6e2b9b05d76e72634348e5a6.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto by Rafael Soldi Photography\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eBest Practice says only the walls of the basement foundation could be repurposed for the rebuild, which replicated its layout, pitched roof, fenestration, and building footprint while adding a small (52-square-foot) mud room through construction.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db58107fa227a702d09b36b885ac8229.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x686\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db58107fa227a702d09b36b885ac8229.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcset=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db58107fa227a702d09b36b885ac8229.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514 1x,https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db58107fa227a702d09b36b885ac8229.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=2 2x, https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/db/db58107fa227a702d09b36b885ac8229.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\u0026amp;dpr=3 3x\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003ePhoto by Rafael Soldi Photography\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/45/45755342858f8a3c5460d03055f55b4a.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=1028\" data-size=\"1028x687\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://archinect.gumlet.io/uploads/45/45755342858f8a3c5460d03055f55b4a.jpg?auto=compress%2Cformat\u0026amp;enlarge=true\u0026amp;w=514\" srcse